Center: IAEA Nuclear Data Section, Vienna, Austria
title: Cross sections for (n,2n) reactions at 14.8 MeV.

x4freetext: Cross sections for (n,2n) reactions at 14.8 MeV.
Neutron yield of approximately 10**9 n/sec were
End-window beta-counter of 4 cm dia., with a
mica window of 4 mg/cm*2 thickness. The length of the
counter was kept only 3 cm to reduce the background,
which was 15 counts/min when the counter was properly
Error in the neutron flux measurement
was estimated to be about 2% in most of the cases, but
could go up to 5% in some cases.
Error in the total number of nuclei in the
target nucleus was estimated to be about 0.5%.
- Statistical error was about 3%. In a few cases
of high counting rate the statistical error was as
small as 2% and in case of low counting rate
-Error due to the presence of thermal neutrons and
measurements of irradiation time and the time which
lapses between the stopping of irradiation and the
start of the counting. These times could be measured
to better than 1% accuracy. The detection of
gamma-rays by the beta counter is another source of
error. The error due to these sources was estimated
TMK. Convert from Iso-quant to Reaction
formalism, reaction corrected in subent 12, added some
EN, EN-RSL moved from subents 002 - 022 to Common
SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
changed to Decay-data, Data-err changed to Err-T
VS. Reaction code corrected in subent. 017
VS. SF4 and DECAY-DATA corrected in 016.
